text:
New York park goes to the dogs for 25th Halloween dog parade 
Winners show off ‘Day of the Dead’ theme 
400 dogs, owners participate A pug in a penguin costume participates in the annual Tompkins Square Halloween Dog Parade on Saturday in New York. Dressed as dinosaurs, a bumble bee, a skeleton and every action hero imaginable, dogs of all types and sizes competed Saturday for attention and prizes in the 25th Halloween Dog Parade. Mary Altaffer Associated Press Ruby Reising, a border collie in a Rihanna at the 2015 Grammys red carpet costume participates in the annual Tompkins Square Halloween Dog Parade on Saturday in New York. Mary Altaffer Associated Press Eric Launder in a piano costume and his pomeranian Simon in a Liberace costume participate in the annual Tompkins Square Halloween Dog Parade in New York on Saturday. Hundreds of dogs took part in what's billed as the nation's largest Halloween dog parade. Mary Altaffer Associated Press Danny Cox, left, with his Chihuahua Paco, Alice Woodroof, center, with her Chihuahua Pearl and Amy Cox with her Yorkshire Terrier Penelope, all from Dallas, Texas, wear Day of the Dead costumes in the annual Tompkins Square Halloween Dog Parade in New York on Saturday. Hundreds of dogs took part in what's billed as the nation's largest Halloween dog parade. Mary Altaffer Associated Press Paralyzed rescue dogs Maury, right, and Little Miss Lexi in Google Maps street view car costumes participate in the annual Tompkins Square Halloween Dog Parade in New York on Saturday, Oct. 24, 2015. Hundreds of dogs took part in what's billed as the nation's largest Halloween dog parade. Hundreds of dogs took part in what's billed as the nation's largest Halloween dog parade.
